The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning to teach a robot to perform pick and place tasks in a manufacturing environment. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of machine learning algorithms and sensors such as cameras and tactile sensors suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The mention of a constantly changing manufacturing environment suggests a need for control systems (cs.SY) to ensure the robot can adapt to new conditions.
